        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 1:06PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>Afternoon temperatures in the upper 80s to near 90 will combine
with high humidity to bring several hours of heat index readings
near 100 degrees this afternoon and early evening. By late
afternoon, isolated thunderstorms are expected to provide some
relief, along the heavy rainfall rates.

If you plan to be outside, avoid prolonged exposure to the heat
or strenuous activity. Drink plenty of fluids to avoid
dehydration.
</description>
